<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Tournament Reports</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Tournament Reports</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/treports/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/treports/treports.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/treports/treports.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/kha_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Cedar Grove, NJ 1/26/02<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.82)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=577'>Kimberly "Arwen Even*" Caton</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=577&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> January 29, 2002</font><p align='justify'><blockquote><font class="bfont"> So, I hadn&#39;t been to a LotR tournament in Cedar Grove yet (I used to play SW there all the time) since I unfortunately bartend on Saturday nights.  However, my bar was closed this weekend due to &quot;electrical system emergency,&quot; and as wrong as it sounds to say &quot;sweet,&quot; I was pretty happy.  Even better, my dad could go since my mom was away with her sisters for the weekend.<br>
   So we get there with time to spare, to be greeted by the news that the TD was planning on allowing the Balrog as tournament legal -- fortunately, myself and another PC that I had just met (Steve Balbo) managed to convince him that that was an incorrect call (whew).  I&#39;m playing Nazgul with rangers and archery, starting Arwen and rare Legolas.<br>
<br>
Game 1: vs. Steve Balbo<br>
Well, I settled in to play my new acquaintance:)  It looked like he was playing something similar to mine, but he had a heavier focus on Aragorn and his toys and stories.  The game started out pretty nondescript, I bid and went first, but was stopped at site 2 by a big black guy with a sword.  He got slowed down by 2 big black guys:)  It got interesting when he hit site 5 -- I was safely at Lorien and he moved onto the Bridge.  He was facing 3 Nazgul -- Nertea, Enquea, and... Toldea, maybe?  His Aragorn has his sword, his bow, and the Saga of Elendil, and there&#39;s Frodo and 1 more character there (Boromir, I think).  He exerts the bow to hit Nertea -- All Blades Perish.  He does it again -- All Blades Perish again.  He uses his last 2 shots to kill him, but now he&#39;s taken 4.  He sends Aragorn up against Toldea, plays a Swordsman to bring him to 12, and tries to sack the Saga to push him to a 14.  I then point out to him that that would automatically kill him, since he has 4 wounds.  He smacks himself in the head, Aragorn dies, and Frodo gets taken out in fierce combat.  My win.<br>
<br>
Highs: weird card tech<br>
Lows: none<br>
<br>
Game 2: vs. Anastasia ?<br>
wow, I get to play a girl for the first time!  She was playing Moria with an Aragorn focus.  I go first and double move into Rivenedell, despite losing Arwen at site 2 to an Ancient Chieftain with a pair of Drums in the Deep (doh!).  On her turn I drop Nelya and convert her sites 2 and 3 to my sites 2 and 3 -- Weatherhills and Bruinen.  This prohibits her from making the double move.  I have Sting out, so on my turn I know she&#39;s holding a Cave Troll (ick).  I luckily get my mirror combo out, do it twice, and do NOT get the troll.  I elect to stop there since she had insufficient twilight to bring him out that turn, and maybe I&#39;ll get him on my next shot.  I do:)  She&#39;s limited to one move a turn for the rest of the game and I use the mirror to get rid of most of her minions.  I hit site 9 while she&#39;s at 5 or 6.  My win.<br>
<br>
Highs: playing a girl, the mirror (strong even post-errata)<br>
Lows: losing Arwen at site 2.<br>
<br>
Game 3: vs. Mark?<br>
so this guy tells me that this is his first tournament, and his first time playing against a non-starter deck.  Tempting to underestimate him, but I don&#39;t do that.  He was playing hobbit healing with Moria.  He bids 5 and obviously goes first, moving to site 3 in one shot since I&#39;m holding nothing.  He kills my Arwen at site 2 with the same trick I lost her to in the last game, except I was hlding a DEfiance to save her and didn&#39;t use it (doh!).  He&#39;s limited to pretty much one move a turn for the rest of the game, playing his hobbits and pump cards very well (I was impressed, it&#39;s not an easy deck).  I use Toldea to pick off Sam and Pippin, and cut down his orcs with archery and Thror&#39;s Mao to stay away from the Anduin Wilderland at site 7.  I hit site 9 while he&#39;s at 7.  My win.<br>
<br>
Highs: winning?<br>
Lows: forgetting Arwen&#39;s Defiance<br>
<br>
Game 4: vs. my dad (Bob Caton)<br>
great, I love driving 2 hours to play my dad!  He&#39;s playing power Nazgul with all of the pumper cards with Aragorn, the elves, and the dwarven allies for a Shoulder to Shoulder healing circle.    We tie for thebid but I win the coin flip to go first.  My opening hand is GREAT -- Last Alliance, Gwemegil, Ranger&#39;s Sword, rare Boromir...  He brings down Cantea at site 2.  And I have my weapons, great.  I decide to take a risk and exert Legolas to hit Cantea twice (no exertion) and take him out with Aragorn.  I decide to risk the double move, and get to the Ford uneventfully.  I didn&#39;t see another Nazgul until the Bridge.  His Fellowship has the Mirror, allies, and Shoulder to Shoulder working (he gets my Witch King), but I use a pair of Beauty is Fadings to get rid of the Mirror and Shoulder to Shoulder.  I get away with double moves, he does not.  I&#39;m at 9 while he&#39;s back at 6.  My win.<br>
<br>
Highs: beating my dad<br>
Lows: beating my dad<br>
<br>
Game 5: vs. Kevin?<br>
He&#39;s playing Nazgul with a fellowship start identical to mine.  I bid and go first, then take a burden to play Aragorn from my draw deck.  Then I realize that I had him in my hand.  Then his turn he comes down with a Nazgul and a sword, who is now damage +1 thanks to my 3 burdens.  Grrr...  Aragorn and Arwen both take 2 wounds.  But I gotta keep moving, I have ARV in my hand, and he SHOULD be playing the Ford... thank God.  He brings down another baddie, but they get exhausted and I use Legolas to pick them off.  He moves only once on his turn.  I have enough of a jump on him at this point that I can probably get away with moving slowly, which I do and my fellowship stays in good shape.  He loses a mess of companions at sites 4 and 5, and moves into Lorien with a naked Frodo.  Unfortunately, he had JUST gotten Sting in his hand and only gave me 5 twilight, so I couldn&#39;t ovewhelm him that turn.  However, he went down on his next turn, when he had to leave the safety of the trees...  I was at site 8 when he was overwhelmed.  My win.<br>
<br>
Highs: 5-0<br>
Lows: That Aragorn thing<br>
<br>
So I win as the only undefeated, Mike Dalton takes second as the only 4-1, and my dad gets third as the highest 3-2.  I pull from my packs a Celeborn, a rare Boromir, a foil Sting, a Morgul Gates... great rares.  I also manage to trade for 2 PATHS, 3 Hates, and a Desperate Defense.  Altogether a satisfactory day.<br>
<br>
Props:<br>
   The TD for ultimately making the right call on the Balrog.<br>
   Those packs the store had, hot gosh darnit!<br>
   Kevin, for wanting those foils of mine:)<br>
<br>
Slops:<br>
   None, unless you count the people who should have come but didn&#39;t.  (You know who you are!) <br></font></blockquote><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php?id=3314&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/treports/treports.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
